def: One who determines. [R.] Sir T. Browne.
One who, or that which, controls, governs, or determines. SirP. Sidney.
In a voluntary manner; of one's own will; spontaneously.
A gown or case of skin, or one trimmed or lined with fur.[Obs.]
A small, swift-sailing vessel, propelled by oars and lateensails, -- once common in the Mediterranean.
A grandfather. [Obs.] Writ of Ayle, an ancient English writwhich lay against a stranger who had dispossessed the demandant ofland of which his grandfather died seized.
Earlier form of Acknow. [Obs.] To be aknow, to acknowledge; toconfess. [Obs.]

Such portion of any quantity, as when taken a certain number oftimes, will exactly make that quantity; as, 3 is a part of 12; -- theopposite of multiple. Also, a line or other element of a geometricalfigure.
